{
  "texts": [
    "In conjunction with a feature importance plot, a PDP can be produced which showcases the relative influence a particular feature has on the outcome.",
    "These are also model agnostic and explain the average effect features have on the outcome.",
    "Like a feature importance plot, PDPs can be used to sense check results against the practitioner's business sense.",
    "The PDP shown in Figure 6 can be interpreted as new cars adding approximately CU 220 to the risk premium, whereas older cars add approximately CU 120, all else remaining equal.",
    "The net effect is CU 100."
  ]
}